 EVALUATION PROCEDURES                                            3243 1451
                                                                  3243 1451
 Adopted procedures are based on careful theoretical analysis     3243 1451
 utilizing available experimental data, including optical model   3243 1451
 parameter search and nuclear reaction model calculations.        3243 1451
                                                                  3243 1451
 OM parameter search was performed to reporduce measured total    3243 1451
cross section for natural Ge with the code CCOM by O. Iwamoto.    3243 1451
                                                                  3243 1451
 Nuclear reaction model calculations were performed with the      3243 1451
 code EMPIRE-II by M. Herman [He01, He02]. This is modularized    3243 1451
 statistical model code that integrates into a single system a    3243 1451
 number of important modules and features:                        3243 1451
                                                                  3243 1451
 - Spherical OM (code SCAT2 by O. Bersillone), and deformed OM    3243 1451
   including coupled-channels model (code ECIS03 by J. Raynal).   3243 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including HRTW width         3243 1451
   fluctuation correction.                                        3243 1451
 - Qauntum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION & TRISTAN by     3243 1451
   H.Lenske), and MSC NVWY model.                                 3243 1451
 - Exciton model (code DEGAS by E. Betak). This code represents   3243 1451
   good approximation to DSD capture model.                       3243 1451
 - Iwamoto-Harada cluster emission model (code PCROSS).           3243 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of each particle,    3243 1451
   including realistic treatment of discrete transitions.         3243 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL-2 library [Ri03].             3243 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses, level density, 3243 1451
   discrete levels, OM parameters and gamma strength functions.   3243 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (utility code EMPEND by A. Trkov), coupled   3243 1451
   to grahpical presentation (utility code ZVView by V.Zerkin).   3243 1451
                                                                  3243 1451
                                                                  3243 1451
 PARAMETERIZATION                                                 3243 1451
                                                                  3243 1451
 Optical model                                                    3243 1451
 - SCAT2 code used for spherical OM parameterization.             3243 1451
 - For neutrons OM by Wilmore-Hodgson was modified to reproduce   3243 1451
   total cross section for natural Ge.                            3243 1451
   ----------                                                     3243 1451
   U=47.76-0.228*E-0.00118*E**2                                   3243 1451
   W=9.17-0.053*E                                                 3243 1451
   V_so=7.0                                                       3243 1451
   r_u=1.297-0.00076*A+4e-6*A**2-8e-9*A**3                        3243 1451
   r_w=1.269-0.00037*A+2e-6*A**2-4e-9*A**3                        3243 1451
   r_so=r_u                                                       3243 1451
   a_u=0.66                                                       3243 1451
   a_w=0.48                                                       3243 1451
   a_so=a_u                                                       3243 1451
   ----------                                                     3243 1451
 - For protons, OM by Koning-Delaroche (RIPL-2:OMP-2405)          3243 1451
 - For alpha particles, OM by V.Avrigeanu et al.(RIPL-2:OMP-9600) 3243 1451
                                                                  3243 1451
 Level densities and discrete levels                              3243 1451
 - Gilbert-Cameron level densities were used with energy dependent3243 1451
   a-parameter proposed by Ignatyk.                               3243 1451
   The asymptoticvalue of the a-parameter is calculated by the    3243 1451
   systematics of Iljinov et al.                                  3243 1451
 - Discrete levels were taken from RIPL-2 level file that is      3243 1451
   based on the 1998 version of the ENSDF database.               3243 1451
                                                                  3243 1451
 Other parameters and tuning                                      3243 1451
 - ECIS03 with DWBA option was used to account for direct         3243 1451
   contribution to low lying 2+ and 3- discrete levels in (n,n'). 3243 1451
   Deformation parameters were taken from work of (p,p') analysis 3243 1451
   [Ke92].                                                        3243 1451
 - Preequilibrium components were calculated using the following  3243 1451
   options: Multistep direct and multistep compound models with   3243 1451
   default parameters for neutron channel, exciton model with     3243 1451
   angular momentum coupling (DEGAS) for proton and gamma         3243 1451
   channels, cluster emissin model by Iwamoto and Harada (PCROSS) 3243 1451
   for alpha channel                                              3243 1451
 - Gamma-ray strength function of modified Lorentzian version 1   3243 1451
   (MLO1) by Plujko in RIPL-2 was used.                           3243 1451
